<paragraph blockId="256.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257">
USNM 
<number box="[286,360,440,464]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="87457.0">87457</number>
: was examined directly and matches Dall’s description (Pl. 
<number box="[1027,1071,440,464]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="130.0">130</number>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1083,1150,439,464]" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="210.[151,188,1695,1717]" captionTargetBox="[305,1256,193,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@210.[305,1257,193,1592]" captionText="Fig. 2. Holotype, 18.2 x 7.3 mm, F. alba, new species (USNM 1291342). Fig. 3. Paratype, 17.3 x 7.6 mm, F. chaaci (Espinosa &amp; Rolán, 1995) (MNHN 2857). Fig. 4. Holotype, 15.6 x 6.0 mm, F. crocea, new species (UF 155640). Fig. 5. Holotype, 15.3 x 5.4 mm, F. contracta, new species (UF 170316). Fig. 6. Holotype, 13.2 x 5.1 mm, F. petiti Tippett, 1995 (USNM 880073). Fig. 7. Holotype, 27.5 x 11.0 mm, F. phasma (Schwengel, 1940) (ANSP 176453). Fig. 8. Neotype, 25.5 x 9.5 mm, F. fucata (Reeve, 1845) (USNM 1291346). Fig. 9. Holotype, 25.0 x 7.4 mm, F. elongata, new species (UF 155626). Fig. 10. Holotype, 21.2 x 7.4 mm, F. tippetti, new species (UF 155639). Fig. 11. Holotype, 16.8 x 7.4 mm, F. marmarina (Watson, 1881) (NHMUK 1887.2.9.103). Fig. 12. Lectotype, 17.8 x 5.8 mm, F. pagodula (Dall, 1889) (USNM 87471)." pageId="256" pageNumber="257">
Fig. 
<number box="[1134,1150,439,464]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
), except that it is smaller, 
<number box="[151,188,476,500]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="5.1">5.1</number>
, not 
<quantity box="[243,332,477,500]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="256.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257">
None of the examined specimens exactly match the 
<quantity box="[804,893,512,535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
length described by Dall. The drawing in Dall (
<number box="[160,220,548,573]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="1889.0">1889</number>
a: pl. 
<number box="[280,308,548,572]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="11.0">11</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[367,381,548,573]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="2.0">2</number>
) is very poor, but as explained by Dall, “These shells are so very small and polished that it is extremely difficult for an artist in pure line-work to represent them adequately.” (Dall, 
<number box="[1121,1181,584,608]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="1889.0">1889</number>
a: 
<number box="[1205,1236,583,608]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" value="92.0">92</number>
). Since the length measurements of the examined shells do not agree precisely with Dall’s measurement, and inasmuch as all lots were not examined, no 
<typeStatus box="[413,516,655,680]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation is made here.
</paragraph>
